13:27.881 --> 13:29.448
What he did to me wasn't poetic.

13:29.449 --> 13:30.683
It was filthy.

13:30.684 --> 13:33.618
And I loved it.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

13:33.620 --> 13:36.922
Got to write it down. Go.

13:36.924 --> 13:40.126
I got in his car,
and we just drove for days,

13:40.127 --> 13:43.663
his hand on the wheel,
my head in his lap.

13:43.664 --> 13:47.266
I do love a bench seat.

13:47.267 --> 13:50.269
For the next three months
we wandered the countryside.

13:50.270 --> 13:54.406
Truth be told, he put more miles
on me than he did that Rambler.

14:00.646 --> 14:02.281
(door opens)

14:02.282 --> 14:03.516
MIKE: Hey.

14:03.517 --> 14:04.783
Look who's feeling better.

14:04.784 --> 14:06.284
Hey.

14:06.286 --> 14:08.587
Whew, what is that smell?

14:08.588 --> 14:10.356
Your mother's five-garlic soup.

14:10.357 --> 14:15.493
Oh, I hope you drank it,
'cause sh-she'll rub it on you.

14:15.495 --> 14:18.429
I went the oral route.

14:18.431 --> 14:20.165
Look at you, writing again.

14:20.166 --> 14:23.034
Yeah, a new story about
a young girl coming of age

14:23.036 --> 14:26.738
on a hardscrabble farm at the
base of the Mudlick Mountains.

14:26.740 --> 14:28.006
Mudlick? Th-That's weird.

14:28.007 --> 14:31.008
My mom grew up on a farm
in Mudlick.

14:33.512 --> 14:35.814
Aw, no!

14:35.815 --> 14:38.317
Mike, her story is incredible.

14:38.318 --> 14:40.118
Do you know she ran
away from home

14:40.119 --> 14:42.120
at 16, with a city feller,

14:42.121 --> 14:44.556
and went on a
cross-country crime spree?

14:44.557 --> 14:46.658
(chuckles)

14:46.659 --> 14:50.227
Wait, what?!
Yeah. Yeah.

14:50.229 --> 14:52.030
Yeah, I mean, it was... it was
petty crime... shoplifting,

14:52.031 --> 14:54.633
siphoning gas, not paying for
haircuts, that sort of thing,

14:54.634 --> 14:56.168
but...
(chuckles)

14:56.169 --> 14:59.471
<i>My</i> mother?
Yeah.

14:59.472 --> 15:01.807
They were hiding in
abandoned buildings and barns

15:01.808 --> 15:03.441
with your grandfather
hot on their trail.

15:03.442 --> 15:06.210
Believe me, their trail
was "H-O-T" hot.

15:06.212 --> 15:09.314
I don't think
I want to know what that means.

15:09.315 --> 15:12.683
Well, then you better
not read our book.

15:12.685 --> 15:14.618
"Our"?

15:14.620 --> 15:17.054
Yeah, she's writing it with me.

15:17.056 --> 15:19.658
Wha...

15:19.659 --> 15:22.026
Mike, your mother
has a great story,

15:22.028 --> 15:24.094
and I want to be the one to help
her tell it. So you're gonna

15:24.096 --> 15:25.196
spend the next six months

15:25.197 --> 15:27.064
working side-by-side
with my mother?

15:27.066 --> 15:28.600
Oh, it's gonna take
at least a year,

15:28.601 --> 15:30.335
and more than a few
trips to Mudlick.

15:30.336 --> 15:35.306
I want to put my hands in the
dirt that sprouted Peggy Biggs.

15:35.307 --> 15:40.144
Okay, well...
good luck with that.

15:40.145 --> 15:44.749
Just a heads up, I-I think
the farm's a Walmart now.

15:44.750 --> 15:46.150
That's fine.

15:46.151 --> 15:49.686
I'll just go to the Garden
Center and grab a bag of mulch.

15:51.000 --> 15:57.074
Advertise your product or brand here
