16:01.979 --> 16:04.146
Here we are, ladies.
Okay.

16:04.148 --> 16:07.317
Can I get you two anything
to drink?

16:07.318 --> 16:10.087
I'd take a Sanka, if you got it.

16:10.088 --> 16:12.788
I don't know what that is.

16:12.790 --> 16:15.357
Just get her something hot
and bitter.

16:16.893 --> 16:17.994
You said you were trying

16:17.995 --> 16:19.396
to picture me as a young girl?

16:19.397 --> 16:22.299
There I go.

16:22.300 --> 16:24.234
Ladies.
MOLLY: Oh!

16:24.235 --> 16:26.102
Xander, I would like
to introduce you

16:26.103 --> 16:28.404
mmother-in-law, Ms. Peggy Biggs.

16:28.406 --> 16:32.475
So, this is what became of the
lost little girl from Mudlick.

16:32.476 --> 16:33.977
Yep, I...
Shh!

16:33.978 --> 16:36.880
Let me drink in that face.

16:36.881 --> 16:39.482
The permanently-etched scowl,

16:39.483 --> 16:41.351
the deep lines of disapproval

16:41.352 --> 16:44.087
in the forehead,
the eyes that once loved

16:44.088 --> 16:47.223
but are now filled
with silent judgment.

16:47.224 --> 16:49.124
Listen, princess...

16:49.926 --> 16:51.194
...I might have a few lines,

16:51.195 --> 16:53.396
but I canola oil this face
every night.

16:53.397 --> 16:56.498
It's as soft
as a catcher's mitt.

16:58.600 --> 16:59.802
She's magnificent!

16:59.803 --> 17:02.037
Right? I mean...

17:02.039 --> 17:04.773
can you imagine the story that
turned that sweet little girl

17:04.775 --> 17:06.776
into this?

17:06.777 --> 17:08.211
(Xander clears throat)

17:08.212 --> 17:11.614
I have to admit, I am rather
intrigued by the story.

17:11.615 --> 17:13.182
Oh, I'm so glad, but...

17:13.183 --> 17:16.252
just so you know,
so is Simon & Schuster.

17:16.252 --> 17:18.488
What?
Y-You went to them first?

17:18.489 --> 17:21.924
After the book launch
I gave you?!

17:21.925 --> 17:25.461
Well, I mean, we really want
to work with you, but...

17:25.462 --> 17:28.064
you're gonna have to be
willing to work with us.

17:28.065 --> 17:32.400
Show us the money, twinkle toes.

17:37.240 --> 17:38.808
(quietly): This is negotiating.
Just play it cool.

17:38.809 --> 17:40.408
(quietly): Gotcha.

17:44.580 --> 17:47.782
(both gasp, squeal, laugh)

17:48.718 --> 17:51.252
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

17:52.054 --> 17:55.169
Is this your final offer?

17:55.170 --> 17:59.380
It wasn't, but it is now.

17:59.381 --> 18:02.291
Oh, and we were lying about.

